The numbering of the substituents on the piperidine ring indicates the position of the methyl and methoxy groups, while the prefix "oxy" denotes the presence of an ether group. The molecular formula provides a concise representation of the relative number of atoms of each element present in the compound, thereby facilitating its identification and classification within the realm of organic chemistry.
